Socar Will Finance Building of $300 Million Soccer Stadium in Azerbaijan

-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 
2011-02-18T12:31:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/socar-will-finance-building-of-300-million-soccer-stadium-in-azerbaijan.html
State Oil Co. of  Azerbaijan , also
known as Socar, will finance a $300 million soccer stadium the
former Soviet republic plans to build outside the capital Baku,
company spokesman Nizamaddin Guliyev said by phone today.  The stadium, which is set to become the country’s biggest
with 65,000 seats, will be based on the Stade de  France  near
Paris, Youth and Sports Minister Azad Rahimov said in comments
broadcast on state television.  Socar Chief Executive Officer Rovnag Abdullayev heads
Azerbaijan’s Association of Football Federations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zulfugar Agayev at 
 zagayev@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
